---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import PostCard from "../../components/PostCard.astro";
import { getCollection } from "astro:content";

const posts = (await getCollection("blog")).sort(
  (a, b) => b.data.date.valueOf() - a.data.date.valueOf()
);
---

<BaseLayout title="Blog | Dare to Break Free">
  <section class="page-hero">
    <p class="eyebrow">Blog</p>
    <h1>Most people only tell the cleaned-up version once they know how the story ends.</h1>
    <div class="intro-copy">
      <p>This blog isn't that.</p>
      <p>A few come from memories I thought I'd buried properly. Others come from things I'm still trying to understand in real time.</p>
      <p>The good days, the messy ones, the moments where things finally make sense, and the moments where they completely don't.</p>
      <p>Some of it will probably make you uncomfortable. Hopefully, parts of it will make you feel a little less alone.</p>
      <p>Nothing here is about pretending to have the perfect answer.</p>
      <p>It's about being honest about the process.</p>
      <p>Because sometimes the most powerful thing you can hear is that someone else has felt it too.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="post-grid">
      {posts.map((post) => <PostCard post={post} />)}
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
